Master of Education in Australia for International Students: Best Universities, Requirements, Costs and Scholarships

  • 345 Reads
  • 3 min Read
  • By:CANAM Group
  • Updated On:Jun 02,2023 01:05 PM IST

Australia is known to offer excellent opportunities for international students seeking to pursue a Master of Education degree. Read the blog to know everything about the degree program, including universities offering the course, admission requirements, tuition fees and available scholarships.

 A Master of Education (M.Ed.) in Australia is a postgraduate degree that focuses on advanced studies in the field of education. The degree is designed for educators and professionals looking to deepen their knowledge, enhance their teaching skills, and explore leadership opportunities in education. The M.Ed. programs in Australia are well-regarded globally, and graduates often find employment in various educational settings, including schools, universities, government agencies, and non-profit organizations.

To know more about M.Ed in Australia, continue reading the blog.

Why Study a Master of Education in Australia?

Some of the important reasons to consider pursuing this degree in Australia include:

  • Australia is popular for its world-class education system, with numerous universities ranking highly in global university rankings
  • The country offers a wide range of M.Ed. programs, allowing students to choose from general degrees or specialized tracks focusing on areas such as early childhood education, special education, educational leadership, or TESOL
  • Studying in Australia provides international students with a new perspective on education, as the country's education system incorporates both global best practices and innovative approaches
  • Australia’s rich multicultural diversity enriches the learning experience for international students
  • Post completion of M.Ed in Australia, international students may be eligible to apply for a post-study work visa, allowing them to work for up to two years in the country after graduation
  • University Teachers in Australia are paid the highest globally
    List of Universities offering M.Ed Courses in Australia

Below are some of the popular universities offering a range of M.Ed courses in Australia:

  • La Trobe University
  • University of Wollongong
  • University of South Australia
  • Monash University
  • Edith Cowan University
  • University of Melbourne
  • University of New South Wales
  • Victoria University
  • University of Adelaide
  • RMIT University

Program Structure and Duration

M.Ed. programs in Australia typically take 1-2 years to complete, depending on the length of the course. The program structure may vary depending on the university, but generally, it includes a combination of coursework, research projects, and practical experience.
Coursework generally covers the following topics:

  • Curriculum Design and Development
  • Educational Psychology and Learning Theories
  • Educational Research Methods
  • Assessment and Evaluation
  • Educational Leadership and Management
  • Educational Policy and Reform
  • Inclusive education and special needs education

In addition to the general M.Ed. programs, some universities offer specialized degrees or tracks that focus on specific areas, such as early childhood education, special education, educational leadership, or TESOL (Teaching English to Speakers of Other Languages).

Requirements for International Students to Study Master of Education in Australia

  • Most universities require a bachelor's degree in education or a related field of study with a minimum GPA score. The required score varies from institution to institution, so students need to check the admission details with their study-abroad consultants
  • International students must prove their English proficiency through giving language tests like IELTS, TOEFL, or PTE
  • Some universities may require teaching experience or other relevant professional experience in the field of education

Application Process to Study M.Ed in Australia

The application process for an M.Ed program in Australia usually involves the following steps:

  • Research and select a suitable program and university
  • Submit an online application through the university's application portal, along with the required documents such as academic transcripts, English language test scores, CV, LOR, SOP etc.
  • Wait for an offer of admission
  • Accept the offer and secure a Confirmation of Enrolment (CoE) required to apply for an Australian student visa
  • Begin with the visa application process (requiring students to provide evidence of financial capacity, health insurance, and a valid passport, among other documents)

Costs of Studying Master of Education in Australia

Tuition fees: The estimated cost to pursue a Master of Education program in Australia ranges between AUD 25,000 and AUD 60,000 per year for international students, depending on the university and course duration.

Living expenses: The cost of living in Australia depends on where students choose to stay, with major cities being more expensive. On average, students need approximately AUD 20,000 to AUD 25,000 per year to pay for living expenses, including accommodation, food, transportation, and personal expenses.

Master of Education in Australia: Scholarships

There are many scholarship options for international students pursuing a Master of Education (M.Ed.) in Australia. Such financial aid options help students to cover a range of expenses, including tuition fee, living expenses, and other costs linked with studying abroad. Some of the popular scholarships for international students are:

Australia Awards Scholarships: Funded by the Australian government, these scholarships are awarded to students from developing countries and cover tuition fees, airfare, living expenses, and other costs. The eligibility criteria and application processes for the scholarship may, however, vary on the basis of the applicant's country of citizenship.

Endeavour Leadership Program: This program provides financial support for high-achieving students to pursue postgraduate studies in Australia. The scholarships cover tuition fees, living allowance, travel allowance, and health insurance.

University-specific scholarships: As the name suggests, these scholarships are offered by Australian universities to international students on the basis of their academic performance, financial need, or other criteria. A few examples of these scholarships include:

  • University of Sydney International Scholarships
  • University of Melbourne Graduate Scholarships
  • Monash University International Merit Scholarships
  • University of Queensland International Scholarships
  • Australian National University (ANU) Scholarships for International Students

Destination Australia Scholarships: Funded by the Australian government to attract international students these scholarships offer up to AUD 15,000 per year for tuition fee and living expenses.

Steps to find and apply for scholarships:

In order to apply for scholarships in Australia, international students must follow the following steps:

  • Search about the different types of scholarships offered by the Australian government
  • Check eligibility criteria and application deadline for each scholarship and find whether these are accepted in the applied university
  • Prepare a well-written scholarship application, including a personal statement or essay highlighting academic achievements, career goals, and reasons for choosing to study in Australia
  • Obtain letters of recommendation from teachers, professors, or employers who can vouch for the academic and professional abilities
  • Keep in mind to submit the scholarship applications before the deadlines with the required supporting documents

Note: Since the competition for scholarships can be intense, students should apply for multiple scholarships to increase their chances of receiving financial support.

Conclusion

Pursuing a Master of Education in Australia offers international students a rewarding and enriching experience and proves to be a great investment for their future career.

While there are many top universities that offer excellent program options, students find the application process to be complex and complicated. This is why it is always suggested that students get their profile assessed by expert study abroad consultants who can offer guidance in the best way possible.

FAQ

What is the minimum CGPA requirement for a Master in Australia?
The CGPA requirement for a master's degree in Australia varies from institute to institute. While some require a score of $.0 or above, others may require a minimum score of 60% for bachelor’s degree.
How much does it cost to study Master's in Australia for international students?
The tuition fee depends on the discipline a student chooses to study and the type of university they wish to apply for. The estimated fee for a bachelor's degree ranges between AUD$20,000 and AUD$45,000* per year and for master's and PhD degrees it ranges between AUD$22,000 – AUD$60,000* per year.
*Note: The estimated figures may change in the near future.
What is the duration of a master of teaching in Australia?
The length of the course depends on whether it is a full-time or part-time course. If the degree is for full-time, the course lasts two years, but in case of part-time, the course lasts four years.
How to apply for an M.Ed degree in Australia?
To make an application for a master’s degree in Australia, students must have a bachelor’s degree in the relevant field of study. It is suggested that students seek the guidance of a study abroad consultant to make an error-free application.
Which is a better place to study - Australia or Canada?
Both Australia and Canada are popular study-abroad destinations among international students. Making a choice between these countries is a personal decision that students make keeping the following factors in mind: tuition fee, living expenses, culture, safety, location, immigration rules and more.
